{"questionId":"9083813","questionHtml":"<p>Ball 1 is dropped from rest from an initial height <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math>. At the same instant, ball 2 is launched vertically&nbsp;upwards at an initial velocity <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/f7744fbff8d2ba49957169814ff4b1fcb849956a.png\"></p>\n<p>At what time are both balls at the same distance above the ground?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>u</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>u</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mi>u</mi></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>h</mi></mrow><mi>u</mi></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9083813","referenceCode":"22N.1A.SL.TZ0.3","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Ball 1 is dropped from rest from an initial height h. At the same instant, ball 2 is launched vertically upwards at an initial velocity u. At what time are both balls at the same d","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"3","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["A. Space, time and motion","A. Space, time and motion","A.1 Kinematics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}